w","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.16 of the Composable Architecture, but there has been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a change to the underlying behavior of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of. When using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"type":"text","text":", if your key does not contain the characters “.” or “@”, then changes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to that key in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":" will be observed using key-value observing (KVO)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used to observe changes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KVO is a far more efficient way of observing changes to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":" and it works cross-process,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as from widgets and app extensions. However, KVO does not work when the keys contain “.”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or “@”, and so in those cases we must use the cruder tool of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":". That is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as efficient, and it forces us to perform a thread-hop when the notification is posted before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"we can update the "},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value. For this reason it is not possible to animate changes that are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"made directly to "},{"code":"UserDefaults","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","